After a jury finds him not guilty of the kidnapping and attempted murder of a former patient, the mentally disturbed Dr. Albert Beck vows to rehabilitate himself. When he lands a teaching job at a prestigious Arizona medical school, he develops a crush on a new student, Melissa, and struggles to keep his growing obsession from taking control of his life.
